  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/deliveroo/b43f3941-25dd-4758-8299-0a0253bfbcfd/application",
    "company": "Deliveroo",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "5b47774a16585297",
    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "SENIOR MARKETING MANAGER, DELIVEROO PLUS (MATERNITY COVER)\n\nJoin us in our mission to transform the way people shop and eat, where impact, innovation, and growth drive everything we do. Our Brand \u0026 Experience team builds the emotional connection between Deliveroo and our customers, riders, and partners. With a deep understanding of our audience and a passion for creativity, we bring our brand to life across every touchpoint. Whether it’s a push notification, social campaign, or packaging design—we craft compelling experiences that shape perceptions, spark engagement, and make Deliveroo a loved, global brand.\n\nWe’re looking for a Senior Marketing Manager, Deliveroo Plus to join our Middle East team for a fixed-term maternity cover contract. In this role, you will own the end-to-end marketing strategy for Deliveroo Plus across the UAE, Kuwait, and Qatar, driving subscriber acquisition and long-term loyalty.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BE DOING\n\nYou’ll be joining the Middle East Marketing team. You will be the primary owner of the Deliveroo Plus growth engine, collaborating with local and international teams to refine our subscription value proposition and hit ambitious commercial goals.\n\nHere’s what your day-to-day might look like:\n\n - Subscriber Acquisition: Develop and execute multi-channel marketing strategies to drive new sign-ups, focusing on converting free-trial users into long-term paid subscribers.\n\n - Retention \u0026 Loyalty: Implement sophisticated lifecycle marketing and personalised experiences to reduce churn and deepen customer engagement with the Plus programme.\n\n - Data Analysis \u0026 ROI: Closely monitor KPIs and acquisition costs (CAC) to optimise channel performance and ensure marketing spend is delivering maximum value.\n\n - CVP \u0026 Pricing Strategy: Partner with Product and Central teams to refine subscription packages, trial offers, and the overall Customer Value Proposition (CVP).\n\n - Campaign Optimisation: Lead the planning and testing of creative assets and marketing messages, using a \"test, learn, and scale\" approach to improve ROI.\n\n - Global Collaboration: Work across geographies, aligning local Middle East initiatives with global Plus strategies to ensure a consistent and high-quality brand experience.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED TO THRIVE\n\nOur ideal candidate is a growth-obsessed marketer who thrives on data and possesses the operational grit to manage high-volume workstreams.\n\n - Extensive Expertise: Minimum 10 years in growth marketing, with at least 4 years specifically focused on subscription-based models.\n\n - Analytical Mastery: High proficiency in data analysis and customer segmentation, with the ability to turn complex data into actionable growth tactics.\n\n - Digital Marketing Depth: Proven experience in paid and owned media, CRM, and Conversion Rate Optimisation (CRO).\n\n - Strategic Influence: Ability to use customer insights to build long-term retention strategies and influence senior stakeholders across different geographies.\n\n - Execution at Pace: A track record of delivering high-quality work with speed and accuracy in a fast-paced, sometimes ambiguous environment.\n\n - Collaborative Spirit: Excellent communication skills with a passion for building relationships and motivating cross-functional teams.\n\n\nWHY JOIN US?\n\nAt Deliveroo, you’ll do work that matters, solving real-world problems in a three-sided marketplace that’s constantly evolving. We’re food lovers, problem solvers, community builders and more, brought together by a shared drive to make things better. Working here you can expect to:\n\n🔧 Make a visible impact every day\n\nYour work directly improves experiences for customers, partners and riders.\n\n🌱 Learn fast in an entrepreneurial environment\n\nWork close to the market with autonomy, pace and real responsibility.\n\n🧠 Build a career, not just a role\n\nStretch yourself, develop new skills and grow as the business evolves.\n\n🌎 Deliver together in an inclusive culture\n\nCollaborative, values-driven teams that support how you work best.\n\nWe aim to create a fair process that lets your skills shine—our interview typically includes 3-4 stages. Find more about how we hire here https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/how-we-hire/.\n\n\nOUR GLOBAL STRUCTURE\n\nDeliveroo is now part of DoorDash, bringing together teams with even greater reach, scale, and ambition. Depending on your role, you may collaborate with teammates, systems, and leaders across DoorDash and Wolt. Together, we’re unlocking new possibilities as one global team.\n\n\nDIVERSITY, EQUITY AND INCLUSION\n\nAt Deliveroo, we know that a great workplace reflects the world around us and that true diversity and inclusion make us stronger, more creative, and better at what we do. We’re committed to fostering an environment where everyone can do their best work and feel they belong.\n\nWe believe in equality of opportunity and welcome candidates from all backgrounds regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, socio-economic background, religion, or belief.\n\nIf you have a disability or long-term health condition and need support to apply for one of our roles, or require any reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, you’ll have the opportunity to let us know once you’ve submitted your application. We’ll share details on how to request support so we can ensure you have a fair and equitable experience.\n\nIf you’re excited about making a real impact in a fast-moving marketplace and growing your career alongside ambitious, supportive teams, we’d love to hear from you!",
